        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 7:54PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 753 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Auburn, moving south at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Midland, Auburn, and Freeland around 800 PM EDT.
Saginaw around 830 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Nelson, Laporte, Swan
Creek, Shiawassee National Wildlife Refuge, Carrollton, Garfield,
Hemlock, Buena Vista Township, Poseyville, and Willard.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
